&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;* Please only apply if your are fully qualified with a PIN registered under the NMC or have this pending *&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to work for a forward thinking organisation who puts patients first, has safety and quality at the heart of everything they do, invests and develops their workforce, encourages innovation and supports positive change then you’re ready to join us at East Lancashire Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are offering you the opportunity to join our nursing team as a Band 4 Nursing Associate on our 20 bedded Diabetic and Endocrinology Ward. You will be given a structured orientation program and preceptorship from our dedicated team of Practice Educators to further develop your skills, confidence and competencies in patient care. We look forward to meeting you and supporting you in your new role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note this post is for a qualified position.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Clare Grice on &lt;strong&gt;01254 732334 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
